OL,3,CFerry in auto-pilot for collision
OL,4,Cwhich killed three, prosecution say
OL,6,FAdvocate Maletroit explains that Mr
OL,7,FCarr was the senior officer on duty,
OL,8,Fwith Mr Sevash-Zade acting as the
OL,9,Fship's lookout and it was their "sole
OL,10,Fresponsibility" to ensure the ferry
OL,11,Fwas safely navigated to Jersey with no
OL,12,Fone else on the command deck at the
OL,13,Ftime.
OL,15,FDespite advanced equipment, the
OL,16,Fprosecutor argues that their behaviour
OL,17,Fshows multiple failures to maintain
OL,18,Flookout, monitor the L'Ecume II's
OL,19,Fposition once they sighted her, assess
OL,20,Fthe risk of collision and then act to
OL,21,Favoid it.
